<subSubSection id="C3261DE06663FFFA1984FE15FEADEE02" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B834E6B6663FFFA1984FE15FEADEE02" blockId="7.[192,784,261,639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B94892796663FFFA1984FE15FE85EDC3" box="[240,348,422,446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Remarks</emphasis>
. Another European species that has been widely introduced in North America, 
<emphasis id="B94892796663FFFA1B82FE74FCC9EDA3" box="[758,784,455,478]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">P.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3C35E86663FFFA19B4FE54FE9AED83" baseAuthorityName="Latzel" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[192,323,487,510]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Polydesmus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polydesmida" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inconstans">
<emphasis id="B94892796663FFFA19B4FE54FE9AED83" box="[192,323,487,510]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">inconstans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should also be expected in municipalities and urban environments in these states, though not as commonly as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C35E86663FFFA1B7CFD94FD5AEE43" baseAuthorityName="C. L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[520,643,550,574]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Oxidus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="B94892796663FFFA1B7CFD94FD5AEE43" box="[520,643,550,574]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">O. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Gonopodal illustrations are available in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6663FFFA1B58FDF5FD03EE23" author="Blower, J. G." box="[556,730,582,606]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref13294" refString="Blower, J. G. 1985. Millipedes. Synopses of the British Fauna (New Series) 35: 1 - 242 + i-vii." type="journal article" year="1985">Blower (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6663FFFA19B4FDD5FEA9EE02" author="Shelley, R. M." box="[192,368,614,639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="1638 - 1663" refId="ref15671" refString="Shelley, R. M. 1988. The millipeds of eastern Canada (Arthropoda: Diplopoda). Canadian Journal of Zoology 66: 1638 - 1663." type="journal article" year="1988">Shelley (1988)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
